For scenario b, it modifies the previous character (i-1) when i and i-1 are same. So for the first scenario (a), when i is 1 to length-1:

if a[i] == a[i-1], then flip a[i], increment a1. For scenario b, when i is from length-1 down to 1:

if b[i] == b[i-1], flip b[i-1], increment a2. So the key difference is which character is being flipped (current vs previous) and the direction of iteration (left to right vs right to left). So in Fortran, let's model this.
